summary: 01/06/1993: Unknown perpetrators bombed a Muslim-owned cafe in Sjenica, Serbia. No one was injured in the explosion, however the cafe was damaged.
propcomment: The explosives blew a hole in the ceiling and destroyed the interior of the cafe.
addnotes: Muslims suspected that the attack may have been a continuation of those carried out during 1992 in Montenegro, when explosives damaged 40 Muslim businesses within a few months in the town of Pljevlja. Officials suspected that this attack might have been aimed at changing the ethnic structure in the area.
scite1: “Muslim-owned café in Sandzak damaged by explosion,” Islamic Republic News Agency, January 9, 1993.
